{"title_page": "Wrestling at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Qualification", "text_new": "{{main|Wrestling at the 2012 Summer Olympics}}\nThis article details the [[Wrestling at the 2012 Summer Olympics]] qualifying phase.\n\nThe '''Wrestling''' competition at the 2012 Games included 344 athletes. Each competing nation was allowed to enter a maximum of 18 competitors (1 per event).<ref name=\"FILA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fila-official.com/images/FILA/documents/jeux_olympiques/110620_London_2012_Qualification_System_EN.pdf|title=Qualification System \u2013 Games of the XXX Olympiad|publisher=[[International Federation of Associated Wrestling Styles|FILA]]|accessdate=20 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n3 places were reserved for Great Britain as host nation, but Great Britain decided to use only one of them<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/wrestling/18276251|title=London 2012: Andy Hunt defends Olga Butkevych's credentials|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=31 May 2011|date=31 May 2011}}</ref> and a further 3 invitational places were decided by the Tripartite Commission. The remaining 338 places were allocated through the qualification process, in which athletes won quota places for their respective nation.<ref name=\"FILA\" />\n\n==Summary==\n{{Wrestling2012Olympics}}\n\n==Timeline==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=300|Event !! width=200|Date !! width=230|Venue\n|-\n| [[2011 World Wrestling Championships|2011 World Championships]]<ref name=\"World 2011\">{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924012946/http://www.fila-official.com/images/FILA/resultats/2011/results_09_istanbul.pdf|title=World Championship Senior \u2013 Results|publisher=[[International Federation of Associated Wrestling Styles|FILA]]|accessdate=17 March 2012}}</ref> || September 12\u201318, 2011 || {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]\n|-\n| [[2012 African & Oceania Wrestling Olympic Qualification Tournament|African & Oceania Qualification Tournament]]<ref na