adow Minister of Urban Affairs (2017\u20132018), Deputy Shadow Minister of the Environment (2015\u20132016), [[Minister of Intergovernmental Affairs and Youth (Canada)|Minister of Intergovernmental Affairs]] (2006), [[Minister of Sport and Persons with Disabilities|Minister of State (Sport)]] (2006), MP for [[Wellington\u2014Halton Hills]], Ontario (2004\u2013present), placed fifth in the 2017 Conservative leadership election<ref>{{cite news |last1=Myers |first1=Bryan |title=Will a Halton Hills MP be seeking Conservative leadership? |url=https://www.theifp.ca/news-story/9774691-will-a-halton-hills-mp-be-seeking-conservative-leadership-/ |accessdate=16 December 2019 |publisher=The Independent and Free Press |date=13 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guelphtoday.com/national-news/tory-leadership-race-shaping-up-as-colour-war-suggests-mp-considering-bid-2055061|title=Tory leadership race shaping up as colour war, suggests MP considering bid|website=GuelphToday.com}}</ref>\n*'''[[Christy Clark]]''' \u2013 [[Premier of British Columbia]] (2011\u20132017), Leader of the [[British Columbia Liberal Party]] (2011\u20132017)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/bad-timing-and-rusty-french-skills-why-christy-clark-decided-not-to-enter-the-race-for-conservative-leader|title=Bad timing and rusty French skills: Why Christy Clark decided not to enter the race for Conservative leader &#124; National Post|date=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n*'''[[G\u00e9rard Deltell]]''' \u2013 Shadow Minister of Intergovernmental Affairs (2019\u2013present), Shadow President of the Treasury Board (2017\u20132019), Shadow Minister of Finance (2016\u20132017), Shadow Minister of Employment, Workforce Development, and Labour (2015\u20132016), MP for [[Louis-Saint-Laurent]], Quebec (2015\u2013present), Quebec MNA for [[Chauveau (electoral district)|Chauveau]] (2008\u20132015) and leader of the [[Action d\u00e9mocratique du Qu\u00e9bec]] (2009\u20132012)<ref name=\"cbcpros\">{{c