ck says MacKay a serious contender for Tory leadership|first=Glenn|last=Hicks}}</ref> \n*[[Mike Lake (politician)|Mike Lake]] (MP for [[Edmonton\u2014Wetaskiwin]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MikeLakeMP/status/1223699767148105729|title=Impressive start to the campaign for @PeterMacKay. The ability to rally strong cross-country support is a must for our new leader.|first=Mike|last=Lake|date=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Ben Lobb]] (MP for [[Huron\u2014Bruce]])<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lobb |first1=Ben |title=Proud to support and endorse @PeterMacKay for leader of the Conservative Party of Canada.|url=https://twitter.com/BenLobbMP/status/1220845819965902849?s=20|website=Twitter|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Dave MacKenzie (politician)|Dave MacKenzie]] (MP for [[Oxford (electoral district)|Oxford]])<ref>{{cite web |last1=MacKenzie |first1=Dave |title=Pleased to offer my support to Peter MacKay for leadership of our CPC party. |url=https://twitter.com/DaveMacKenzieMP/status/1218219174771724290 |website=Twitter |accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Phil McColeman]] (MP for [[Brantford\u2014Brant]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/Phil4Brant/posts/865435810561337|title=Phil McColeman|website=facebook.com}}</ref>\n*[[Marty Morantz]] (MP for [[Charleswood\u2014St. James\u2014Assiniboia\u2014Headingley]]; Shadow Minister for National Revenue)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/marty_morantz/status/1234228481606606848|title=Reasons I support @PeterMacKay for leader of the Conservative Party|first=Marty|last=Morantz|date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Paul-Hus]] (MP for [[Charlesbourg\u2014Haute-Saint-Charles]]; Shadow Minister for Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PierrePaulHus/status/1220396409784061952?s=20|title=I have known @PeterMacKay for over a decade.|last=Paul-Hus|first=Pierre|date=23 January 2020|website=@PierrePaulHus|language=en|access-date=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Bob Saroya]] (