 the [[2017 Conservative Party of Canada leadership election|2017 Conservative leadership election]]. Prior to entering politics, O'Toole served as a [[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|captain]] in the [[Royal Canadian Air Force]] and was a lawyer after completing military service.<ref name=\"starpros\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/politics/federal/2019/12/12/rona-ambrose-peter-mackay-erin-otoole-cited-as-possible-contenders-to-replace-andrew-scheer-as-conservative-leader.html|title=Rona Ambrose, Peter MacKay, Erin O'Toole cited as possible contenders to replace Andrew Scheer as Conservative Leader|date=12 December 2019|work=Toronto Star|access-date=12 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n:'''Candidacy announced:''' 25 January 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/davidakin/status/1221100162271121410|title=And @ErinOTooleMP makes it official|last=Akin  |first=David|date=25 January 2020|website=@davidakin|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6461702/erin-otoole-conservative-leadership-bid/|title=Erin O'Toole to announce formal bid for Conservative leadership|last=Jackson|first=Hannah|date=25 January 2020|website=Global News|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n:'''Date registered with Elections Canada:'''\n:'''Campaign website:''' [https://erinotoole.ca/ www.erinotoole.ca]\n;Policies:\n:;Economic\n:*Defund the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]]<ref>{{cite web |title=ADD YOUR NAME: I SUPPORT DEFUNDING CBC |url=https://erinotoole.ca/defundcbc/ |website=Erin O'Toole}}</ref><br>\n:*Repeal the carbon tax<ref>{{cite web |title=NO CARBON TAX |url=https://erinotoole.ca/carbontax/ |website=Erin O'Toole}}</ref><br>\n:*End subsidies for media companies<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Toole |first1=Erin |title=Justin Trudeau helps failing media corporations.I'll help working Canadians.https://www.thepostmillennial.com/erin-otoole-pledges-to-cancel-trudeaus-media-bailout/\u00a0\u2026 |url=https://twitter.com/erinotoolemp/status/1223614891896033281 |website=Twitter |language=en |date=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n:;Foreign\n:*Support creating a [[CANZUK]] agreement on trade<ref>{{cite web |title=CANZUK Deal |url=https://erinotoole.ca/canzuk/ |website=Erin O'Toole |access-date=7 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504033025/http://erinotoole.ca/canzuk/ |archive-date=4 May 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref><br>\n:;Social\n:*Criminalize blocking railways, airports, ports, or major roads, or entrances to businesses or households<ref>{{cite news |title=Erin O\u2019Toole: This is how I would get our country working again {{!}} National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/opinion/erin-otoole-this-is-how-i-would-make-this-country-work |date=26 February 2020 |language=en-CA}}</ref><br>\n:*Use [[Section 33 of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms|the notwithstanding clause]] to impose mandatory minimum sentences for violent crime<ref>{{cite news |title=Jason Kenney endorses Erin O\u2019Toole for leadership of Conservative party {{!}} National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/canada-news-pmn/otoole-mackay-set-to-kick-conservative-leadership-campaigns-up-a-notch |date=5 March 2020 |language=en-CA}}</ref>\n{{Endorsements box\n|df=yes| title = Endorsements of Erin O'Toole\n| list =\n;'''MPs:'''\n*[[Garnett Genuis]] (MP for [[Sherwood Park\u2014Fort Saskatchewan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/notes/garnett-genuis/my-choice-for-conservative-leader/2759957230720081/|title=My Choice for Conservative Leader &#124; Facebook|website=facebook.com}}</ref>\n*[[Dane Lloyd]] (MP for [[Sturgeon River\u2014Parkland]])<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/DaneLloydCPC/videos/183605969589828// Dane Lloyd], Facebook</ref>\n*[[Greg McLean (politician)|Greg McLean]] (MP for [[Calgary Centre]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GregMcLeanYYC/status/1221848820981485568|title=I'm pleased to support @ErinOTooleMP as Leader of the Conservative Party.|first=Greg|last=McLean|date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Alex Ruff]] (MP for [[Bruce\u2014Grey\u2014Owen Sound]]; retired [[Canadian Armed Forces]] Colonel)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlexRuff17/status/1221873145944125445?s=20|title='m honoured to support @ErinOTooleMP for leadership of the @CPC_HQ.|first=Alex|last=Ruff|date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Cathy McLeod]] (MP for [[Kamloops\u2014Thompson\u2014Cariboo]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Cathy_McLeod/status/1232682665712766978|title=I'm proud to be with @ErinOTooleMP and the true blue movement. Let's unit together and take Canada back! 3/3|first=Cathy|last=McLeod|date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Bruce Stanton]] (MP for [[Simcoe North]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/bruce_stanton/status/1228371160473231361|title=2 de 2: Il m\u00e9rite notre appuie, c'est ce dont nous avons besoin \u00e0 travers le Canada afin d'\u00e9lire un gouvernement Conservateur. Je suis fier d'appuyer @ErinOTooleMP|first=Bruce|last=Stanton|date=14 February 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Kenny Chiu]] (MP for [[Steveston\u2014Richmond East]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RmdKenny/status/1235286156138500097|title=Today I'm pleased to announce that I am endorsing @ErinOTooleMP for leader of the Conservative Party of Canada|first=Kenny|last=Chiu|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Stephanie Kusie]] (MP for [[Calgary Midnapore]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/StephanieKusie/status/1235379445017350145|title=My written statement|first=Stephanie|last=Kusie|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Gary Vidal]] (MP for [[Desneth\u00e9\u2014Missinippi\u2014Churchill River]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/GaryAVidal/status/1236078951425925120|title=Happy to be part of the growing team. #momentum #CPC|first=Gary|last=Vidal|date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Larry Maguire]] (MP for [[Brandon\u2014Souris]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ErinOTooleMP/status/1236709774173114368|title=Thanks for the support, @LarryMaguireMP! Let's keep going!|firs